# SYNAPSE — Cursor Agent Rules
# DO NOT MODIFY STACK OR RULES WITHOUT EXPLICIT INSTRUCTION

## References (read relevant section BEFORE implementing anything)
- Full spec:      docs/prompts/SYNAPSE_MASTER_PROMPT.md
- Active plan:    docs/prompts/SYNAPSE_FINISH_LINE.md
- Build order:    Section 20 of SYNAPSE_MASTER_PROMPT.md (60-step plan, ONE step at a time)
- File structure: Section 4  of SYNAPSE_MASTER_PROMPT.md

---

## Stack (locked — do not substitute)

| Layer        | Technology                                              |
|--------------|---------------------------------------------------------|
| Backend      | FastAPI 0.115+, Python 3.12, async everywhere           |
| Vector DB    | PostgreSQL 16 + pgvector (HNSW, RBAC via SQL filter)    |
| Graph DB     | Neo4j 5, async driver, Cypher                           |
| Relational   | SQLAlchemy 2.0 async + Alembic migrations               |
| Cache/Queue  | Redis 7 + Celery                                        |
| LLM          | Ollama (Llama 3 8B, local)                              |
| Embeddings   | sentence-transformers all-MiniLM-L6-v2, 768 dim         |
| Frontend     | Next.js 14 App Router, TypeScript strict, Tailwind, Zustand |
| Auth         | JWT (python-jose) + bcrypt (passlib)                    |
| Containers   | Docker Compose                                          |

---

## Backend Rules (non-negotiable)

- ALL functions have type hints. `Any` is forbidden.
- ALL endpoints have Pydantic request **and** response schemas.
- ALL DB queries are parameterized. **Never** f-string SQL.
- RBAC enforced via SQL `WHERE permission_tag = ANY($N)` — never filtered in Python after the query.
- **Never** use `print()`. Use `structlog` for all logging.
- **Never** hardcode secrets. Use Pydantic `BaseSettings` + env vars.
- ALL external calls have timeouts + tenacity retry (3 attempts, exponential backoff 2–30 s).
- ALL list endpoints support cursor-based or offset pagination.
- ALL async DB work uses async session/connection correctly (no sync calls in async context).
- Schema changes go through Alembic. Never alter tables manually.
- Follow PEP-8. Max line length 100.
- Use `FastAPI Depends()` for dependency injection everywhere.

## Error Handling

- Custom exception hierarchy — all exceptions inherit `SynapseError`.
- Global exception handler catches everything and returns structured JSON. Never expose raw tracebacks to the client.
- Every response carries a `request_id` header for tracing.

---

## Frontend Rules (non-negotiable)

- TypeScript strict mode. `any` is forbidden. Period.
- Every component handles three states: **loading**, **error**, **success**.
- **Never** use inline styles. Tailwind utility classes + CSS variables only.
- Dark mode is the default. Light mode is secondary.
- Self-host all fonts. No external CDN font requests.
- Use `framer-motion` for all animations and transitions.
- Write semantic HTML (`<main>`, `<nav>`, `<article>`, etc.). No div soup.

## UI Design (critical — do not deviate)

| Token           | Value                        |
|-----------------|------------------------------|
| Background      | `#0A0A0F` (dark charcoal)    |
| Accent          | `#00E5CC` (electric cyan)    |
| Display font    | General Sans                 |
| Code font       | JetBrains Mono               |
| Card border     | 1 px solid, 12 px radius, no drop-shadow in dark mode |
| Button radius   | 6 px, bold text, cyan glow on hover |
| Input style     | Bottom-border only, accent color on focus |

**Forbidden:**
- Fonts: Inter, Roboto, Arial, system-ui, or any generic system font
- Styles: purple/blue gradients, rounded cards with drop shadows everywhere, generic "AI dashboard" aesthetics

---

## Quick Reference Checklist (run before every PR)

- [ ] No untyped Python, no `Any`, no `any` in TypeScript
- [ ] No f-string SQL anywhere
- [ ] No `print()` — structlog only
- [ ] No hardcoded secrets
- [ ] Pydantic schemas on every endpoint
- [ ] Async DB calls use async session correctly
- [ ] RBAC filter is in SQL, not Python
- [ ] External calls have timeout + tenacity retry
- [ ] New DB changes have an Alembic migration
- [ ] Frontend components handle loading / error / success
- [ ] No inline styles, no forbidden fonts
- [ ] Exceptions inherit SynapseError, global handler returns structured JSON
